actions.comment:
Thanks for reporting this inconsistency. You're right that the Blazor `SKGLView` is the only GPU-backed view that doesn't expose `GRContext` as a public property — all other implementations (macOS, WPF, WinForms, WinUI, Metal) do.

As a workaround, you can access the context from inside your `OnPaintSurface` callback via `e.Surface.Context`:

```csharp
OnPaintSurface = (e) =>
{
    var grContext = e.Surface.Context as GRContext;
    // create additional surfaces sharing the same context
};
```

This is limited to use within the callback, so it won't help if you need the context outside of paint events. The proper fix would be adding `public GRContext? GRContext => context;` to the Blazor view, matching the other platforms.
